history.content:
I took 53 in my first semester here and 161 in my seventh, for reference.

But I thought 53 was definitely not time-consuming, even though I had a professor who I couldn't learn from (so I ended up teaching myself). A pretty constant level of work (but not much, really. Definitely my lightest-workload course my first semester.) Maybe an hour or two a day on average? 

161 on the other hand is super variable with the workload. Some weeks all I do is read lecture slides and attend discussion, other weeks I'm working on the project for 8 hours a day (coughProject2cough). If you want to turn 161 into a constant-workload class, start everything early and get help at OH! 

I'm more of a pset person so that could be why I found 53 easier.

Can anyone who has taken both of these classes offer their input on the relative workloads of these two classes? I am deciding between these two and want to gauge how much time I would have to put into them. Thanks!
history.subject: CS 161 vs Math 53 workload
